# List of shebangs and how to make them executable from anywhere in the system
```
#!/usr/bin/env bash
```
#!/usr/bin/env python3
```
```
#!/usr/bin/env ruby
```

```
bash script.sh
python3 script.py
ruby script.rb
```


```
check if it worked:

ls -l script.sh

```


``` 
from another directory

chmod +x /path/to/file/script.example
```

```
then you can launch it as such
./script.sh
```

``` 
to remove the executable

chmod -x filename.example
